    # game/sleeping.rpy:91
    old "You take a look at your amulets. For most people, they would be nothing more than trash, but you wouldn’t sell them for a pouch of dragon bones. You use them to shape pneuma to your will. With these little mementos, the few spells you’re familiar with are far more reliable. Who knows, maybe there’s already some power held in them. \n\nYou look at the old, though clean bandages that remember dozens of herbal balms and wounds. You can put them on your hurting muscles, bruises, and scratches, then hum an old song about time, which either heals all wounds, or kills us too soon to let us bother with our problems. After a few hours or so, the linen will warm up, confirming it did its job. \n\nThis tent may not be much, but your spell would make you feel as good as new - though you’d lose some of your energy. "
